      "rich_text": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "content": "After dark we take a walk to a local restaurant run by a lovely woman named Rose. We order the same two fish that we had for lunch but with one nsima and one chapati which is basically a roti. It’s another incredible culinary experience. A British man named Harry joins us and tells us about the six months of adventures and misadventures that he’s had living in Malawi. ",
            "link": null
          },
          "annotations": {
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "strikethrough": false,
            "underline": false,
            "code": false,
            "color": "default"
          },
          "plain_text": "After dark we take a walk to a local restaurant run by a lovely woman named Rose. We order the same two fish that we had for lunch but with one nsima and one chapati which is basically a roti. It’s another incredible culinary experience. A British man named Harry joins us and tells us about the six months of adventures and misadventures that he’s had living in Malawi. ",
